snippet.textDisplay: In the next season of HiLow premise should be: "You get a boring car for your 16th birthday and then you sup it up once you can afford it (or not)". You should be looking for beige Jettas. Preferably 1.8 Turbo. Parents often think "small displacement car = safe and fuel efficient". They have no idea you crank it up to 400hp. You should be doing more engine work like forged pistons, more egressive cams etc. (basically I wanna see the low car explode). Just avoid newer direct injection models with timing chain and plastic tensioners (TFSI), because it will end in tears for both teams (but it will be good YouTube). I know because I own SEAT with such an engine and just did $3k head replacement :]
